onstructing a comparative grapholinguistic framework that provides readers with important tools for studying any writing system. The book emphasizes that grapholinguistics is a discipline in its own right, inviting discussion and further research in this up-and-coming field as well as an overdue integration of writing into general linguistic discussion.  aIssued also in print.  afunded by Schweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aSchriftlinguistik. 4aSchriftsystem. 4aSoziolinguistik. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aGrapholinguistics.  aLiteracy.  aOrthography.  aWriting Systems.1 aDürscheid, Christa, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut2 aSchweizerischer Nationalfonds (SNF)efunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022 Englishz978311099370708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Linguistics 2022z9783110993684oZDB-23-DSP08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertMouton eBook Package 2022z97831107912970 cEPUBz97831107578970 cprintz978311075777440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110757835zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110757835zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110757835/original  a978-3-11-079129-7 Mouton eBook Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-